Switch & Router Basic Configurations: 

1) User Levels	
   - Navigation on the Cisco CLI
	>config terminal	
	>enable

2) Hostname Custom hostname:
Router>
>enable 
>config t
>hostname R1
> R1


3) Banner motd/message:
SW1> 
>enable
>config t
>banner motd Hey, there.


4) Enable password
>enable
>config t
>enable password R1 

5) Enable console line Password when you start console.
SW1:	
>enable 
>config t
>line 0 
>password SW1
>login

6) Line VTY password: 
>config t
>line vty 0 15
>password SW1
>login

7) Exec timeout	Prevent to staying logged in unattended
>enable 
>config t
>line 0 / vty 0-15
>exec-timeout 5 0 

8)Logging Synchronous:
>config t
>line 0 / vty 0-15
>logging synchronous


9) Disabling ip domain looku- Deactivating the disgusting message when you type the wrong command. 
>enable 
>confg t
>no ip domain lookup

10) IP domain name	Basically setting up a domain. 
>enable 
>confg t
>ip domain-name cisco.com
>>ip domain-lookupiDNS lookup for host → ip computer )
>ip name-server 8.8.8.8 (DNS server ip)

11) Username and password	
	When you have a ssh connection you should have a user and password configuration.	
>enable 
>confg t
>user “Admin” password “Admin”

12) Encrypting all passwords	
	Weak encryption method, service password encryption	
>enable 
>confg t
>service password encryption

13)Set Current Clock Time	
enable
clock set hh:mm:ss day month year

14)Set management IP switch
>enable
>config t
>int vlan 1 
>ip address “IP”
>exit
>ip default-gateway 192.168.1


